A TCP connection is uniquely identified by four values:

Client IP
Client Port
Server IP
Server Port

This allows thousands of simultaneous connections without confusion.

Cybersecurity Relevance

Incident responders rely on socket information to trace malware communications, identify infected hosts, and reconstruct attacker activity.

Tools
Wireshark
tcpdump
Zeek
netstat
Blue Team (Defenders)

Process: Analyze connection logs to identify unusual outbound sessions, suspicious destination IPs, or unexpected client-server communications.

End Goal: Detect compromised systems and lateral movement.

Red Team (Attackers)

Process: Blend malicious traffic with legitimate client-server communications to avoid detection.

End Goal: Maintain stealthy communication with compromised hosts.
